===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/ˈdɛ.nɪ.ɡɹeɪt/}}, {{X-SAMPA|/dE.nI.gr\eIt/}}

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|la}} {{term|denigratus|dēnigrātus|lang=la}}, the past participle of {{term|denigrare|dēnigrāre|to blacken|lang=la}}, from {{term|de|dē|lang=la}} + [[nigrare]] 'to blacken (from {{term|niger||black|lang=la}})

===Verb===
{{en-verb|denigrat|ing}}

# {{transitive}} To [[criticise]] so as to [[besmirch]]; [[traduce]], [[disparage]] or [[defame]].
# {{transitive}} To treat as [[worthless]]; [[belittle]], [[degrade]] or [[disparage]].
# {{rare}} To [[blacken]]. <!-- this usage is the literal sense, yet obscure at best -->

